Descripción_Ampliada:
The DSM-ITO-2189 project aimed to provide a Central Denwa Mini (CDM) solution for the Ministry of Development, Social Services, Health and Sports of the Government of MZA. This project required the design, development, and implementation of a mini central office system that could support the growing communication needs of the ministry's offices.

To achieve this goal, our team utilized advanced telecommunications technologies such as IP-based telephony, network management systems, and digital signal processing algorithms to create a highly scalable and reliable CDM solution. The CDM was designed to accommodate up to 500 concurrent calls, providing seamless connectivity for internal communications, emergency services, and external stakeholders.

The project scope included the following specific deliverables: 

* Design and implementation of a CDM system that integrates with existing telecommunications infrastructure;
* Development of a comprehensive network management system for monitoring and controlling the CDM;
* Configuration of IP-based telephony protocols to ensure seamless communication across different devices and networks;
* Implementation of digital signal processing algorithms to optimize voice quality and reduce latency;

Through this project, we achieved concrete results, including:

* Enhanced communication capabilities for the Ministry's offices, enabling more efficient collaboration and service delivery;
* Improved network reliability and scalability to support growing demands;
* Reduced infrastructure costs by leveraging IP-based telephony technologies;

The context of the client and their needs was critical in shaping our approach. The Ministry of Development, Social Services, Health and Sports required a reliable and scalable communication solution that could meet the diverse needs of its offices, from routine communications to emergency situations. By understanding these requirements, we were able to design and deliver a tailored CDM solution that exceeded the client's expectations.
